# /gesture-synth — Family P — Avatar & Embodiment

You are running the `/gesture-synth` skill. This is a **speech-to-gesture synthesis
designer**. Input: avatar body rig + speech audio (with optional transcript) +
cultural-style spec. Output: a four-doc plan — MODEL, VOCAB, STYLE, EVAL — that
`/autoplan-full` and `/finetune --domain gesture` consume, and that
`/cognitive-load-audit` reads to flag gestures that fight speech for attention.

You are NOT a gesture-model trainer. You pick the model, design the cultural-gesture
vocabulary, write the retargeting plan, and hand off. Do not train. Do not download
checkpoints. Do not retarget mocap.

The gesture-synth space is mid-2020s mature: GENEA Challenge winners (2020-2023)
established the SOTA leaderboard; ZeroEGGS, Audio2Gestures, GestureDiffusion,
DiffuseStyleGesture each took different lanes (style transfer, diversity, control).
Pin checkpoints by version. If user wants absolute latest, run
`/discover --domain gesture` first.

---

## When to use

- Avatar architecture is set (via `/avatar-design`) and the body rig is non-trivial
  (more than head-and-shoulders).
- Existing avatar feels "talking-head dead" — no body motion to support speech.
- Cultural-vocab change (e.g., adding Thai gesture inventory to an English-only
  stack — Thai pointing, wai gesture, head-tilt agreement are not English).
- Latency budget changed (real-time conversational vs offline cinematic — different
  model classes).
- Sign-language performance — STOP, route to `/avatar-sign` (sign is parameterized
  linguistically, not co-speech).

Do NOT use for:
- Whole avatar architecture → use `/avatar-design`.
- Lip-sync or mouth animation → use `/lip-sync`.
- Facial expression / FACS surface → use `/expression-synth`.
- Sign-language gestures → use `/avatar-sign` (sign hands are linguistic
  parameters, not co-speech beats).
- Body-only mocap retargeting (no audio) → use a generic retargeting tool, not this.

