## Edge cases

- **Mixed-culture context with conflicting emblems:** the same gesture is
  innocuous in one culture and offensive in another (thumbs-up). Flag, ask user
  to set a default culture, and forbid the gesture in the others.
- **Sign-language context bleeds in:** if the user starts asking about ASL/TSL
  hand shapes, STOP. Route to `/avatar-sign`. Sign hands are NOT co-speech.
- **Real-time + diffusion model:** GestureDiffusion at full denoising steps is
  not real-time. Recommend distilled / few-step variant or lightweight
  Audio2Gestures.
- **Body rig has no hands:** fine deictics need hands. Either downgrade the
  vocab (broad arm pointing only) or upgrade the rig.
- **Cognitive-load-sensitive context (teaching, accessibility):** route through
  `/cognitive-load-audit` mandatorily. Beats are usually fine; iconic / metaphoric
  during dense speech is risky.
- **License conflict:** GENEA challenge winners have varied licenses; check each.
- **Style reference clip required but unavailable:** ZeroEGGS falls back to a
  prompt or fixed config; quality drops noticeably.
- **Retargeting to a stylized 2D body:** ML models output SMPL-X; 2D rigs need a
  whole separate retargeter. Recommend keyframe-based or skeleton-cell-shaded
  pipelines instead; this skill's ML recommendations don't fit.
- **Hall's TSL teaching avatar:** mixed Thai-English content, teaching context.
  Recommend: DiffuseStyleGesture+ trained on Thai presenter data + per-culture
  vocab (Thai dominant, English fallback for code-switch) + `/cognitive-load-audit`
  enabled. Note: TSL fingerspelling and sign content go through `/avatar-sign`,
  NOT this skill.

